	<div class="pxl-item--inner  " data-wow-delay="ms">
		<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most businesses today are producing </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">content</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400">. Videos, posts, reels. But content alone is often forgotten.</span><span style="font-weight: 400"><br /></span><span style="font-weight: 400"> A </span><b>story</b><span style="font-weight: 400">, on the other hand:</span></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">taps into emotions,</span></li><li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">reveals a purpose,</span></li><li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">invites participation.</span></li></ul><p><span style="font-weight: 400">This is why storytelling has emerged as a cornerstone of effective communication — because </span><b>people remember feelings more than facts</b><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>		
